The sample program on the Haxe main page demonstrates a complete misunderstanding of the value of dictionaries. Not exactly inspiring one to learn more.<p><pre><code>    class Test {
      static function main() {
        var people = [
          &quot;Elizabeth&quot; => &quot;Programming&quot;,
          &quot;Joel&quot; => &quot;Design&quot;
        ];
        for (name in people.keys()) {
          var job = people[name];
          trace(&#x27;$name does $job for a living!&#x27;);
        }
      }
    }</code></pre>
